{
  "texts": [
    "If a journal search was unsuccessful, the authors prompted GPT-4 to search for the references.",
    "If all of these attempts failed, the researchers considered the reference to be invalid/non-existent.",
    "To gain further insight into the veracity of GPT-4 citations, references were coded according to the following possible errors: correct author(s), correct year, correct article title correct, correct journal, correct DOI/URL, and existence of the article.",
    "To determine the extent to which factually correct information was provided, both coders independently checked the veracity of each sentence in the following order until they were able to determine the accuracy of the claim: first they read they source article (regardless of whether there were errors in the citation and/ or reference).",
    "If the article did not substantiate the claim each researcher performed a Google Scholar search and examined the first 50 results (some results revealed less than 50), followed by a Google search (using the same criteria)."
  ]
}